print(q.dequeue())  # Output: 'b'
print(q.dequeue())  # Output: 'c'
print(q.dequeue())  # Output: 'a' (raises an exception, as the queue is now empty)
```
This implementation uses two stacks to maintain the front and back of the queue. When an item is enqueued, it is added to the back of the queue (i.e., added to the back_stack). When an item is dequeued, it is removed from the front of the queue (i.e., removed from the front_stack). Since the front and back of the queue are maintained as separate stacks, this implementation ensures that the queue follows the First-In-First-Out (FIFO) order.
